  "doc_id": "38531",
  "text": "For drug efficacy studies using a GEMM of lung cancer, Kras LSL-G12D/+ and Trp53 fl/fl mice (8-12 weeks old) were anaesthetized by intraperitoneal injection of ketamine (80 mg per kg body weight) and xylazine (10 mg per kg body weight) and infected intratracheally with 2.5 × 10 5 infectious particles of Lenti-Cre per mouse, as previously described [CITATION_1] . Mice were evaluated by micro-computed tomography imaging to quantify lung tumour burden before being assigned to various treatment study cohorts. Mice were treated with vehicle, trametinib and/or ponatinib per os for 4 consecutive days followed by 3 days off treatment, at 3 mg/kg body weight and 30 mg/kg body weight, respectively. Micro-computed tomography imaging evaluation was repeated every week during the treatment. Investigators were not blinded with respect to treatment.",
